CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1941, pg. 17 reads: "One Of The Grays' Runs That Beat Baltimore - Here's Whatley, Homestead Grays' husky outfielder, galloping home with one of the runs that beat the Baltimore Elites 3-0 at Forbes Field Saturday. Partlow pitched 5-hit ball and also smacked a homer himself to help the Homesteaders triumph. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Homestead Grays outfielder Dave "Speed" Whatley running to home plate in game against Baltimore Elite Giants at Forbes Field, with Carnegie Institute in background
